    "description": [
        {
            "text": "\"Electric Current Density\" is a measure of the density of flow of electric charge; it is the electric current per unit area of cross section. Electric current density is a vector-valued quantity. Electric current, $I$, through a surface $S$ is defined as $I = \\int_S J \\cdot e_n dA$, where $e_ndA$ is the vector surface element.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
